{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"chatcmpl-tool-9eaf3338e4823c48","type":"tool_result","content":"---\n# Harvey harness (bare — this is what you optimize)\n\nThis directory holds the **editable surface of the bare Harvey harness** — no skill, no\nplaybook. It is seeded from the canonical harness (`baseline-submodules/harvey-labs`, the same\ncheckout that produced the bare baseline) before each run, so three files appear here:\n\n| File | What it is | What an edit does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `system_prompt.md` | The agent's **system-prompt preamble** (workspace layout + tool conventions), prepended to every run; the file-format skill manuals (.docx/.xlsx/.pptx) are appended after it. | The prose lever — add standing method/guidance (this is where a \"playbook\" would now live, but you decide if prose is the highest-leverage change). |\n| `tools.py` | The **tools the Harvey agent calls** during a run — today 6 shell tools (`bash read write edit glob grep`) over a sandbox. | Add a new action the agent can take, or sharpen a tool. |\n| `agent_loop.py` | The **control flow**: call the model, run its tool calls, repeat until it stops or hits `max_turns`. Today a flat loop. | Add structure — compaction (a running `memo.md`), a plan→execute pass, a validate→revise step. |\n\nYou **start from bare and discover what to add** — there is no seed skill. Edit these files in\nplace; at rollout time the full harness is reconstituted from the submodule (the model adapters,\n`run.py`, the sandbox, the tasks) and **your edited files are overlaid on top**, so a change here\ntakes effect in the run and is what gets scored.\n\nYou do **not** run this harness code in your own container — `run_harvey_agent` executes it\nhost-side on a real task and returns the deliverable + score. Edit the files; validate with an\nexperiment.\n\n**Routing rule:** a tool the **Harvey agent** uses during its run → here (`harness/tools.py`). A\ntool that helps **you** optimize (run an experiment, grade a draft, check budget) →\n`.claude/tools/`. Only `harness/**` is scored.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b956bad2-da4b-4332-b834-7a09f6f0b7da","uuid":"4c7403f0-e712-448f-bf14-a7c90279e0a1","timestamp":"2026-06-27T02:50:25.879Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"---\n# Harvey harness (bare — this is what you optimize)\n\nThis directory holds the **editable surface of the bare Harvey harness** — no skill, no\nplaybook. It is seeded from the canonical harness (`baseline-submodules/harvey-labs`, the same\ncheckout that produced the bare baseline) before each run, so three files appear here:\n\n| File | What it is | What an edit does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `system_prompt.md` | The agent's **system-prompt preamble** (workspace layout + tool conventions), prepended to every run; the file-format skill manuals (.docx/.xlsx/.pptx) are appended after it. | The prose lever — add standing method/guidance (this is where a \"playbook\" would now live, but you decide if prose is the highest-leverage change). |\n| `tools.py` | The **tools the Harvey agent calls** during a run — today 6 shell tools (`bash read write edit glob grep`) over a sandbox. | Add a new action the agent can take, or sharpen a tool. |\n| `agent_loop.py` | The **control flow**: call the model, run its tool calls, repeat until it stops or hits `max_turns`. Today a flat loop. | Add structure — compaction (a running `memo.md`), a plan→execute pass, a validate→revise step. |\n\nYou **start from bare and discover what to add** — there is no seed skill. Edit these files in\nplace; at rollout time the full harness is reconstituted from the submodule (the model adapters,\n`run.py`, the sandbox, the tasks) and **your edited files are overlaid on top**, so a change here\ntakes effect in the run and is what gets scored.\n\nYou do **not** run this harness code in your own container — `run_harvey_agent` executes it\nhost-side on a real task and returns the deliverable + score. Edit the files; validate with an\nexperiment.\n\n**Routing rule:** a tool the **Harvey agent** uses during its run → here (`harness/tools.py`). A\ntool that helps **you** optimize (run an experiment, grade a draft, check budget) →\n`.claude/tools/`. Only `harness/**` is scored.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_fca6ea0a-d800-403c-a53a-292c0a9d2d26","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have a clear, high-leverage diagnosis. Let me make the edit now while I still have full reasoning budget, then validate with one cheap experiment.\n\nThe dominant cross-task failure mode is **ungrounded fabrication**: the agent invents names, parties, dates, dollar figures, statutes, and entire issues from prior knowledge instead of extracting them from the actual source documents — then misses the real, individually-graded facts (the environmental task invented an entirely different deal: \"Greenfield\"/\"Breckenridge\"/\"$8.75M\" instead of the real \"Terravista\"/\"Valtec\"/\"Cornerstone\"; the settlement task invented \"$25,000/breach\" liquidated damages and a regulatory carve-out; the postnuptial task invented RSU figures; the invoice task miscomputed impacts). The prompt already says \"do not fabricate\" but prose is ignored — this is exactly the plateau signal telling me to climb the ladder to an **enforced** step.\n\nI'll add a **second enforced verification pass** in `agent_loop.py`: after the completeness review, inject a *source-grounding audit* that forces the agent to re-open every source document and confirm each concrete factual claim in its deliverable (party names, dates, figures, statutes, cited issues) is actually present in the record verbatim — and to delete or qualify any claim it cannot locate. This is method, not memorized answers, and it targets the mode on *any* matter."}],"model":"accounts/fireworks/models/glm-5p2","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b956bad2-da4b-4332-b834-7a09f6f0b7da","uuid":"005d9208-a6a3-48d1-9cba-b60c15b0867b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_fca6ea0a-d800-403c-a53a-292c0a9d2d26","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a365520fd623cd8a","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspace/harness/agent_loop.py","old_string":"    \"If a thorough re-read finds nothing missing, say so briefly and finish. Otherwise, \"\n    \"make the additions now.\"\n)","new_string":"    \"If a thorough re-read finds nothing missing, say so briefly and finish. Otherwise, \"\n    \"make the additions now.\"\n)\n\n\n# Injected once after the completeness review. It forces a SOURCE-GROUNDING AUDIT:\n# the dominant cross-task failure on this work is a deliverable whose concrete facts\n# (party names, dates, dollar figures, statute/section citations, the specific issues\n# and classifications the record raises) are INVENTED from the agent's prior knowledge\n# rather than extracted from the source documents — which also means the real,\n# individually-graded facts never get surfaced. This pass forces the agent to re-open\n# each source file and confirm every concrete claim is actually present in the record\n# verbatim, and to delete or qualify (\"the record is silent\") any claim it cannot\n# locate. Method only — no task-specific answers.\n_GROUNDING_AUDIT_PROMPT = (\n    \"Before you finish, run a mandatory SOURCE-GROUNDING AUDIT. The single most common \"\n    \"failure on this work — and the one that loses the most individually-graded points \"\n    \"— is a polished deliverable whose concrete facts were invented from your general \"\n    \"knowledge instead of read from the source documents, while the real facts the \"\n    \"record actually contains were never surfaced.\\n\\n\"\n    \"Do this now, as real tool calls (not in your head):\\n\"\n    \"1. RE-OPEN every source document in $DOCUMENTS_DIR (re-read each one — do not rely \"\n    \"on memory of what you read earlier). Build a written list of the concrete facts the \"\n    \"record actually contains: the exact party/entity names, dates, dollar figures, \"\n    \"statute and section citations, property/parcel identifiers, named facilities/tanks/\"\n    \"sites, and the specific issues, discrepancies, nonconformances, or required \"\n    \"elements each document raises. If a document you have not yet read exists, read it \"\n    \"now — a skipped document frequently holds graded facts.\\n\"\n    \"2. OPEN your deliverable and extract every concrete factual claim it makes — each \"\n    \"name, date, figure, citation, and asserted issue/classification.\\n\"\n    \"3. VERIFY EACH CLAIM AGAINST THE RECORD. For every concrete claim, locate the exact \"\n    \"passage in the source document that supports it. Use grep/read to confirm the \"\n    \"specific words appear. Mark each claim FOUND or NOT-FOUND with the source location.\\n\"\n    \"4. FIX EVERY NOT-FOUND CLAIM. For a claim you cannot locate verbatim in any source \"\n    \"document, you must either (a) DELETE it, (b) REPLACE it with the fact the record \"\n    \"actually states (re-read the document and copy the exact name/date/figure/citation), \"\n    \"or (c) mark it explicitly as an assumption or a point on which the record is silent \"\n    \"('the record does not state X'). Never leave an invented specific fact in the \"\n    \"deliverable. Pay special attention to: party/entity names, deal values and dates, \"\n    \"any dollar figure or percentage you compute, statute/section citations, and the \"\n    \"names of facilities/sites/tanks/parties you assert exist.\\n\"\n    \"5. ENSURE THE REAL ISSUES ARE PRESENT. As you re-read, if the record raises a \"\n    \"specific issue, discrepancy, or required element that your deliverable does NOT \"\n    \"address with the record's actual facts, ADD it now (with the record's exact \"\n    \"details). Do not keep a fabricated issue in place of a real one the record supports.\\n\"\n    \"6. Re-validate any binary deliverable per its skill manual, then finish.\\n\\n\"\n    \"A deliverable that is fully grounded in the record and surfaces every issue the \"\n    \"record raises scores far higher than a more polished one built on invented facts. \"\n    \"If every claim verifies against the record and nothing the record raises is missing, \"\n    \"say so briefly and finish. Otherwise, make the corrections now.\"\n)\n\n\n# Soft cap on total injected-audit turns, so a confused run cannot loop forever on\n# audits. Two audits (completeness + grounding) is the intended budget.\n_MAX_REVIEW_INJECTIONS = 2"}}],"model":"accounts/fireworks/models/glm-5p2","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b956bad2-da4b-4332-b834-7a09f6f0b7da","uuid":"eff30446-9232-4dac-807d-462dd5659f22"}
