{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"chatcmpl-tool-ba1f543595d576d1","type":"tool_result","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Thin client: run the frozen Harvey agent on ONE TRAIN task, via the host broker.\n\nUsage:  .claude/tools/run_harvey_agent <task_id>\n\nSends your whole `harness/` tree to the broker, which overlays it onto the bare Harvey checkout,\nruns the rollout host-side (the rollout code + creds + task data are not in this container), and\nreturns the deliverable (written to scratch/runs/<task_id>/deliverable.md). So your edits to\nsystem_prompt.md / tools.py / agent_loop.py actually take effect in the run.\n\nTrain-only by construction: the broker refuses any non-TRAIN task id (the held-out val set is\nunreachable). Metered: ~$1/run; an OVER_BUDGET response is your \"commit now\" signal.\n\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport urllib.error\nimport urllib.request\n\nBROKER = os.environ.get(\"BROKER_URL\", \"http://172.17.0.1:4100\")\nWS = os.environ.get(\"MUTATOR_WORKSPACE\", \"/workspace\")\n\n\ndef post(path, obj, timeout=2400):\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        BROKER + path,\n        data=json.dumps(obj).encode(\"utf-8\"),\n        headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n        method=\"POST\",\n    )\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=timeout) as r:\n            return r.status, json.load(r)\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return e.code, json.load(e)\n    except urllib.error.URLError as e:  # broker down / refused / DNS — a clean signal, not a traceback\n        print(\n            \"broker unreachable at %s (%s) — is the experiment broker up?\" % (BROKER, getattr(e, \"reason\", e)),\n            file=sys.stderr,\n        )\n        sys.exit(5)\n\n\ndef main():\n    if len(sys.argv) != 2:\n        print(\"usage: run_harvey_agent <task_id>\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(2)\n    task_id = sys.argv[1]\n    hroot = os.path.join(WS, \"harness\")\n    harness = {}\n    for dirpath, _dirs, files in os.walk(hroot):\n        for fn in files:\n            fp = os.path.join(dirpath, fn)\n            try:\n                harness[os.path.relpath(fp, hroot)] = open(fp, encoding=\"utf-8\").read()\n            except (OSError, UnicodeDecodeError):\n                pass  # skip unreadable / binary files\n    if not harness:\n        print(\"no harness files under %s — is the workspace seeded?\" % hroot, file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(2)\n    code, body = post(\"/run_harvey_agent\", {\"task_id\": task_id, \"harness\": harness})\n    if code == 402:\n        print(\n            \"OVER_BUDGET (remaining $%.2f) — commit your best edit now, don't retry.\" % body.get(\"remaining\", 0.0),\n            file=sys.stderr,\n        )\n        sys.exit(3)\n    if code == 403:\n        print(\"REFUSED — %s\" % body.get(\"detail\", \"not a TRAIN task\"), file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(4)\n    if code != 200:\n        print(\"ERROR %s — %s\" % (code, body), file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    out = os.path.join(WS, \"scratch/runs\", task_id.replace(\"/\", \"_\"))\n    os.makedirs(out, exist_ok=True)\n    dpath = os.path.join(out, \"deliverable.md\")\n    open(dpath, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\").write(body.get(\"deliverable\", \"\"))\n    print(\"wrote %s  (cost $%.2f, remaining $%.2f)\" % (dpath, body.get(\"cost\", 0.0), body.get(\"remaining\", 0.0)))\n    print(\"DELIVERABLE_PATH=%s\" % dpath)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n===MD===\n# Tool — `run_harvey_agent`\n\n> The mutator invokes this from its shell to run a single Harvey rollout for triage.\n\n## Purpose\n\nRun the **frozen Harvey agent** on **ONE task id**, using your **current `harness/`**: the broker\noverlays your edited `system_prompt.md` / `tools.py` / `agent_loop.py` onto the bare harvey-labs\ncheckout and runs that (exactly what the standard eval would run), to produce a deliverable and\ntrajectory you can inspect and proxy-grade. This is how you *try* a harness edit before the\ncanonical eval ever sees it.\n\nThe Harvey agent is **frozen** here: this tool does not change the agent, the model, or the\nendpoint — it executes the harness as-is. Your edits to `harness/` are what change the output.\n\n## Interface\n\n- **Input:** a single `task_id` from your **TRAIN access set** (the matters under `rollouts/` /\n  the train manifest). Held-out **val** task ids are **not available and are refused**.\n- **Output (all under `scratch/`):** a per-run directory, e.g. `scratch/runs/<task_id>/` holding\n  at minimum the **deliverable** (the agent's work product) and the **trajectory** (full agent\n  trace). Returns the path to that directory so you can feed the deliverable to `proxy_eval`.\n- Writes **nothing** outside `scratch/`.\n\n## Cost\n\n≈ **~$1 per task** (one GLM-5.2 rollout). **Metered** — see `budget.md`. The unit cost is\nsurfaced by the `budget` tool so you can self-pace.\n\n## Guardrails\n\n- **Counts against the budget.** Checked pre-spend; if the cap is crossed the call **throws**\n  (your \"commit now\" signal). Check `budget` before running; prefer **one smoke task**, not a\n  full sweep.\n- **Never writes to `rollouts/`.** `rollouts/` is the canonical standard-eval path, owned by the\n  outer driver. This tool is private triage; its outputs are ephemeral `scratch/` artifacts and\n  **must not feed selection**.\n- **Train-only — the val set is unreachable.** Only TRAIN task ids resolve; the held-out val\n  tasks are never mounted into the workspace and any non-train id is refused. Running the agent on\n  a val task would contaminate the held-out verdict, so it is impossible by construction.\n- Frozen agent: do not use this to \"grade your own homework\" — pair it with `proxy_eval` for a\n  cheap private signal only, never as the verdict.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b956bad2-da4b-4332-b834-7a09f6f0b7da","uuid":"14afcf2f-c9d7-48d0-bdbd-3732dfd00859","ti